      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can see that you're doing your research, but I'm not convinced that's enough to justify self-experimentation. You're right that stable INR levels can indicate that your body has adjusted to the dose, but that doesn't necessarily mean it's safe to reduce it. The truth is, warfarin's effects can be subtle and unpredictable, and even small changes can cause significant bleeding risks. I'm not saying it's impossible, but I'm saying it's not worth the gamble. If you're feeling good and your INR is stable, I'd still advise you to consult your doctor before making any changes.",
